-- CIMB falls 0.7 pct after says in merger talks with two smaller lenders 
-- By Al-Zaquan Amer Hamzah
-- Thu Jul 10, 2014 09:05PM EDT
-- None



KUALA LUMPUR, July 11 (Reuters) - Shares of CIMB Group Holdings Bhd <CIMB.KL> fell 0.7 percent on Friday after the company announced plans to acquire two smaller lenders to create the country's largest bank. [ID:nL4N0PL09R]

RHB Capital Bhd <RHBC.KL> was up 7.5 percent while Malaysia Building Society Bhd <MBSS.KL> rose 10.3 percent. The three banks confirmed on Thursday they had obtained approval from the country's central bank to begin merger talks.